### Pact Blade (4e)
Level 3+

Warlocks favor this wickedly sharp blade.

Weapon: Light Blade (usually daggers and sickles)

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd6 damage on crit

Property: This blade functions as a warlock implement, adding its enhancement bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls for warlock powers that use implements. 

Property: When a creature you have cursed with your Warlock’s Curse makes a melee attack against you, deal damage to the creature equal to the pact blade’s enhancement bonus.

Special: You do not gain your weapon proficiency bonus to the attack roll when using a pact blade as an implement.

### Rod of Corruption (4e)
Level 3+

*This rod magnifies and multiplies your Warlock’s Curse.*

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd6 damage on crit

Property: Whenever your pact boon is triggered, instead of taking its normal benefit you can transfer your Warlock’s Curse to each enemy within 5 squares of the original target.

### Rod of Dark Reward (4e)
Level 2+

*This rod channels your Warlock’s Curse while adding to your defenses.*

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd6 damage on crit

Property: Whenever you place a Warlock’s Curse on an enemy, you gain a +1 power bonus to AC until the start of your next turn.

### Rod of Death’s Grasp (4e)
Level 23+

*A rod that ripples with necrotic energy.*

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, on crit: 10+ ongoing necrotic damage (save ends), and you gain 10+ temp hp

Power (Daily ✦ Necrotic): Free Action. Use this power when you place your Warlock’s Curse on a target. The target takes ongoing 10 necrotic damage (save ends). Each time this damage is dealt, you gain 10 temporary hit points.

### Rod of Harvest (4e)
Level 14+

This rod stores the power of your pact boon so that you can unleash it when you want to.

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd6 damage on crit

Property: When your pact boon is triggered, you can store its effect within your rod instead of using it immediately. Your rod can hold only one pact boon effect at a time.

Power (Encounter): Minor Action. Use the pact boon effect stored within your rod.

### Rod of Reaving (4e)
Level 5+

This rod enhances the damage dealt to those suffering your Warlock’s Curse.

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd8 damage on crit

Property: When you place your Warlock’s Curse on a target, the creature takes damage equal to the rod’s enhancement bonus.

### Rod of the Pyre
Level 10+

This rod crackles with arcane fire.

Standard +X to attack/damage rolls, +Xd6 fire damage on crit

Power (Daily): Free Action. When you place your Warlock’s Curse on a target, the creature gains vulnerability 2 fire until the end of your next turn.
